{
  "texts": [
    "Striking a balance between obtaining comprehensive longitudinal data and minimizing patient burden remains a critical challenge.",
    "As technology advances and methodologies evolve, optimizing data collection methods and addressing associated limitations will be instrumental in leveraging the full potential of longitudinal data for refining TDTs and improving patient outcomes in the realm of RPTs.However, we should emphasize that developing TDTs might have challenging issues in terms of acquiring patient data, developing models, estimating parameters, and addressing ethical considerations.",
    "Since cancer is a complex disease and also RPT mechanisms are not fully investigated, the interaction of radiopharmaceuticals with this system, their pharmacokinetic and pharmacodynamic, should be studied and analyzed through advanced modalities.",
    "Despite the challenges, TDTs offer a promising research framework for studying RPTs in an in-silico ecosystem.",
    "To effectively integrate TDTs into clinical practice, a thorough and collaborative approach involving researchers, medical physicists, technologists, and clinicians is essential."
  ]
}